---
import Layout from "../../../../layouts/index.astro"
---

<Layout>
	<p>
		Compares <code>operand</code> to <code>test</code> (a
		<code>Number</code> or <code>Integer</code>) and returns a function that
		takes an optional <code>arg</code> and uses it as the operand or injects a argument
		from some other source (e.g., HTML element, query string, session storage).
	</p>
	<p>
		When called, the returned function returns the operand if it is
		&gt;/&lt;/===/etc. the test value, otherwise returns an
		<code>Error</code>.
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>IsEqualTo</strong>
			<code
				>= (datatype = "Number") =&gt; operand =&gt; test =&gt; (arg =&gt;
				Either&lt;Error, Number | Integer&gt;)</code
			>
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>IsLessThan</strong>
			<code
				>= (datatype = "Number") =&gt; operand =&gt; test =&gt; (arg =&gt;
				Either&lt;Error, Number | Integer&gt;)</code
			>
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>IsMoreThan</strong>
			<code
				>= (datatype = "Number") =&gt; operand =&gt; test =&gt; (arg =&gt;
				Either&lt;Error, Number | Integer&gt;)</code
			>
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>IsNoLessThan</strong>
			<code
				>= (datatype = "Number") =&gt; operand =&gt; test =&gt; (arg =&gt;
				Either&lt;Error, Number | Integer&gt;)</code
			>
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>IsNoMoreThan</strong>
			<code
				>= (datatype = "Number") =&gt; operand =&gt; test =&gt; (arg =&gt;
				Either&lt;Error, Number | Integer&gt;)</code
			>
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>IsUnequalTo</strong>
			<code
				>= (datatype = "Number") =&gt; operand =&gt; test =&gt; (arg =&gt;
				Either&lt;Error, Number | Integer&gt;)</code
			>
		</li>
	</ul></Layout
>
